(44, 8, 25, 44, 20, 21, 21, 'testified and preached the word of the Lord', 'Connection of Testifying and Preaching', 'Both passages emphasize the act of testifying and preaching the gospel. Acts 8:25 highlights preaching in Samaria, while Acts 20:21 focuses on testifying to Jews and Greeks about repentance and faith.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 8, 25, 42, 9, 52, 56, 'preached the gospel in many villages', 'Samaritan Reception of the Gospel', 'Both passages emphasize the interaction with Samaritans. In Acts, the apostles preach the gospel in Samaritan villages, while in Luke, a Samaritan village rejects Jesus. This connection highlights the contrasting responses to the message of salvation.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 8, 25, 43, 15, 27, 27, 'preached the gospel', 'Witnessing and Preaching Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of bearing witness. Acts 8:25 describes the apostles preaching the gospel, while John 15:27 speaks of their role as witnesses due to their close relationship with Jesus.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 8, 25, 44, 1, 8, 8, NULL, 'Witnessing in Samaria', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of witnessing in Samaria. Acts 1:8 outlines the geographical scope of the apostles'' mission, while Acts 8:25 demonstrates their fulfillment of this directive by preaching in Samaritan villages.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
